// Here we are going to only keep the opening hours for week days (Monday to Friday) and also split them so that for each business
// we will get an array similar to [("10:30", "19:30"), null, ("10:30", "19:30"), ("10:30", "19:30"), ("10:30", "19:30")] (here there's no opening data for Tuesday for instance)
val operatingHours = spark.sql("""
SELECT
  business_id,
  state,
  city,
  neighborhood,
  array(split(hours.Monday, '-'), split(hours.Tuesday, '-'), split(hours.Wednesday, '-'), split(hours.Thursday, '-'), split(hours.Friday, '-')) as hours
FROM businesses
WHERE state IS NOT NULL
AND city IS NOT NULL
AND neighborhood IS NOT NULL
""")
operatingHours.createOrReplaceTempView("operating_hours")
operatingHours.printSchema

paragraphs.text:
%sql
-- Here we do three things in the same query (from inner to outer):
--   1. exploding the hours which means that for each business we get a separate row per day of the week
--   2. splitting opening and closing times and converting to minutes so that we have numeric columns for which to calculate percentiles
--   3. calculating the percentiles per state, city, neighborhood only keeping the triplets for which we have at least 5 entries
-- We will need to turn the result from minutes back into a time (mod 60 to get the hours, reminder to get the minutes).
-- The result suggest we can lowercase the state, city and neighborhood to better group the data (should be done earlier as exploding will multiply the number of rows)
SELECT
  state,
  city,
  neighborhood,
  percentile(day_opening, 0.5) AS median,
  percentile(day_opening, 0.95) AS 95th
FROM (
  SELECT
    state,
    city,
    neighborhood,
    split(day_operating_hours[0], ':')[0] * 60 + split(day_operating_hours[0], ':')[1] AS day_opening,
    split(day_operating_hours[1], ':')[0] * 60 + split(day_operating_hours[1], ':')[1] AS day_closing,
    day_operating_hours
  FROM (
    SELECT
      state,
      city,
      neighborhood,
      EXPLODE(hours) AS day_operating_hours
    FROM operating_hours
    ORDER BY 1
  )
  WHERE day_operating_hours IS NOT NULL
)
GROUP BY 1, 2, 3
HAVING count(3) > 5
ORDER BY 1, 2, 3
